# Rules

- Never modify core WordPress files. Use hooks and filters instead.
- Escape all output using `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `esc_url()`, etc.
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs (`sanitize_text_field()`, `wp_kses()`).
- Use prepared statements (`$wpdb->prepare()`) for database queries.
- Secure AJAX and REST API endpoints with nonces (`check_ajax_referer()`).
- Restrict direct file access using `defined('ABSPATH') || exit;`.

